our preconceptions of ‘realism’. Striving for the all-important quality of truth in everything he does, Leigh has consistently shown how ordinary lives are too complex to fit snugly into the conventions of narrative art. From the bittersweet observation of Life is Sweet or Secrets and Lies, to the blistering satire of Naked and the manifest compassion of Vera Drake, he has demonstrated a matchless ability to perceive life’s funny side as well as its tragedies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aMotion picture producers and directorszGreat BritainxCriticism and interpretation. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Entertainment & Performing Arts.2bisacsh  aBritish cinema.  aLife is Sweet.  aMike Leigh.  aNaked.  aSecrets and Lies.  aVera Drake.  afilm director.  arealism.  asurvival mechanism.  atelevision.1 aWhitehead, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779198640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847791986423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847791986/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles